parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key falls out of the ignition
the key becomes stuck in the ignition
and the security system activates preventing the vehicle from starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turn signals can cause accidents or near-misses due to the lack of visibility to other drivers.
symptoms: The turn signals fail to operate
the hazard lights need to be used to temporarily correct the failure
and the hazard lights make a buzzing or crackling noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: and the warning lights on the instrument panel illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turn signal/hazard light switch can cause the turn signals to malfunction, leading to accidents or traffic violations, and potentially causing a distraction while driving.
symptoms: The turn signals or hazard lights do not function
with a clicking or ticking noise coming from the dashboard. In some cases
causing smoke to emit from the steering column.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold gasket can cause coolant and oil to leak into the cylinders, leading to engine damage, overheating, and potential engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Coolant and oil leaking into the cylinders

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the Passlock system can cause the engine to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: and the engine not turning over.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
The failure of the cooling system can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
The malfunction of the turn signal/hazard light system can cause accidents or reduce visibility, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Intermittent or inoperative turn signals/hazard lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause extended stopping distances, accidents, or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Grinding or squealing noise when applying brakes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold gasket can cause coolant leaks, engine overheating, and engine damage.
The failure of the security system can cause the vehicle to not start, or the security light to flash, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
